descriptions.amount_off: A positive integer representing the amount to subtract from an invoice total (required if `percent_off` is not passed).
descriptions.currency: Three-letter [ISO code for the currency](https://stripe.com/docs/currencies) of the `amount_off` parameter (required if `amount_off` is passed).
descriptions.duration: Specifies how long the discount will be in effect. Can be `forever`, `once`, or `repeating`.
descriptions.duration_in_months: Required only if `duration` is `repeating`, in which case it must be a positive integer that specifies the number of months the discount will be in effect.
descriptions.expand: Specifies which fields in the response should be expanded.
descriptions.id: Unique string of your choice that will be used to identify this coupon when applying it to a customer. If you don't want to specify a particular code, you can leave the ID blank and we'll generate a random code for you.
descriptions.max_redemptions: A positive integer specifying the number of times the coupon can be redeemed before it's no longer valid. For example, you might have a 50% off coupon that the first 20 readers of your blog can use.
descriptions.name: Name of the coupon displayed to customers on, for instance invoices, or receipts. By default the `id` is shown if `name` is not set.
descriptions.percent_off: A positive float larger than 0, and smaller or equal to 100, that represents the discount the coupon will apply (required if `amount_off` is not passed).
descriptions.redeem_by: Unix timestamp specifying the last time at which the coupon can be redeemed. After the redeem_by date, the coupon can no longer be applied to new customers.
